            <div class="credit" data-image-credit="Courtesy Nrityagram" ></div>
            <div class="caption">Nrityagram Resident Faculty: Guru Surupa Sen and Pavithra Reddy</div>
        </div>
        <p>
            Odissi training is led by <a href="/surupa" class="bodylink">Surupa Sen</a>, Artistic Director of the Nrityagram Dance Ensemble, and <a href="/pavithra" class="bodylink">Pavithra Reddy</a>, Director of Educational and Outreach Programmes. Both have lived, studied, and practised at Nrityagram for over three decades, carrying forward its evolving pedagogy with depth and continuity.
        </p>
        <p>
            Yoga sessions are conducted by Jaya Chakravarty, a practitioner and teacher with over twenty years of experience, and founder of The Practice Room, Bangalore.
        </p>
    </div>
</div>
<div class="container">
    <div class="wrapper flow">
        <h1 class="center">Training</h1>
        <div class="image-plus top-flow portrait">
            {% image "https://res.cloudinary.com/nrityagram/image/upload/v1776006874/summer-workshop-anoushka_ipy4kk.jpg",
      "Nrityagram Summer Workshop: Guru Surupa Sen conducting a class",
      ["560", "768", "1046"] %}
            <div class="credit" data-image-credit="Courtesy Nrityagram" ></div>
        </div>
        <p>
			Days are rigorous and immersive. Participants engage in over five hours of daily practice, entering a rhythm that is both demanding and sustaining. 
		</p>
        <p>
			The training includes:
            <ul>
                <li>Foundational Odissi technique</li>
                <li>Yoga and physical conditioning rooted in traditional practices and the <em>Natyashastra</em>
                </li>
                <li>Rhythmic structures specific to Odissi</li>
                <li>Study of classical texts such as the <em>Abhinaya Darpana</em>
                </li>
            </ul>
        </p>
        <p>
            In the spirit of the Gurukula, learning extends beyond the studio. Participants share responsibility for daily life - caring for their spaces, maintaining the environment, and attending to the rhythms that support collective living.
        </p>
    </div>
</div>

<div class="container accent-bg">
    <div class="wrapper flow">
        <h1 class="center">Living at Nrityagram</h1>
        <div class="image-plus top-flow">
            {% image "https://res.cloudinary.com/nrityagram/image/upload/v1583857821/6-Kula_fldxvp.jpg",
            "Kula Residence",
            ["560", "768", "1046"] %}
            <div class="credit" data-image-credit="Rupert Lorhalder" ></div>
            <div class="caption">Kula Residence</div>
        </div>
        <p>
			Set across a ten-acre campus on the outskirts of Bangalore, Nrityagram is both a place of study and a living, breathing artistic home.
		</p>
        <p>
            Here, architecture rests lightly on the land. Studios open into trees, pathways follow the contours of the earth, and silence is as present as sound. The space invites a different pace - one that allows attention to deepen.
        </p>
        <p>
            To live here, even briefly, is to experience how the environment shapes practice, and how practice, in turn, begins to shape the self.
        </p>
    </div>
</div>

<div class="container">
    <div class="wrapper flow">
        <h1 class="center">Food</h1>
        <p>
            Meals are vegetarian, simple, and nourishing - prepared with ingredients sourced from our gardens and nearby farms.
        </p>
        <p>
            While we are unable to accommodate specific dietary preferences, the food is designed to support the physical demands of training: balanced, wholesome, and lightly spiced.
        </p>
    </div>
</div>
<div class="container accent-bg">
    <div class="wrapper flow">
        <h1 class="center">The Nrityagram Ensemble</h1>
        <p>
            Nrityagram is an active residential community of dancers, teachers, and long-term students engaged in sustained practice.
        </p>
        <p>
            During the workshop, participants may have the opportunity to observe rehearsals of the ensemble and resident students. These moments offer a closer view into the discipline, precision, and evolving artistic process that shape the work. Access may be requested with the faculty.
        </p>
    </div>
</div>
